          %br
          (#{underlying "saa{b+}lč-či{f+}s"} → #{underlying "saa{b+}lč-n-či{f+}s-I{f}"})
      %p Finally, n-class nouns with final /k g s/ (which drop before the plural ending) keep the -n- in the lative, translative, and ablative, the result of paradigmatic levelling{2}.
      %ul
        %li #{t "лоок", "look"} ‘thorn’ → #{t "лоон", "loon"} ‘thorns’
        %li #{t "лоокәҥ", "lookəŋ"} ‘thorn (#{underlying "#{abbrev 'tra'})’"} → #{underlying "#{t "лоонәҥы", "loonəŋy"} ‘thorns (#{abbrev 'tra'}"})’
        %li #{t "киис", "kiis"} ‘wolf’ → #{t "киин", "kiin"} ‘wolves’
